From Kenneth Whitehead Subject Letter to the President Here's a copy of a letter I'm e mailing to the Slickster at his address of To William Clinton President of the United States of America President I am writing to express my utter outrage at the conduct of various government agencies in regards to the tragedy in I DEMAND the dismissal or resignation of Lloyd Bensen Secretary of the Treasury who bears responsibility for the initial helicopter and grenade attack by the ATF against the Branch Davidians and of Janet Reno who authorized the final assault on the very day that we were commemorating the Warsaw ghetto And I would truly appreciate it if you would make sure something like this never happens again on your Respectfully yours Kenneth Whitehead Get involved It's your Let's take it I will be much more willing to believe the Government's side of the Waco story AFTER we are allowed to hear from the So far all we've gotten has been censored by the very people who have the most to cover And I'd REALLY like to know how they got the press who complained so loudly about being kept off the front lines during the Gulf War be such obedient lap dogs in Kind of makes me wonder if this so called freedom of the press isn't highly Ken Whitehead